The teachable concept here is the PPL `date` matcher (time-limited grants). That criterion is implemented only in the Pomerium Zero/Enterprise policy engine (pomerium-console pkg/policy/criteria/date.go), not in open-source Pomerium Core. The sealed harness runs Core from a config file, which rejects it at startup with "unknown policy criterion: date", so the time-window enforcement cannot be sealed here. Verified manually with the Zero Console (allow before a future date; 403 after) and against the jit-example app's API-driven grants. A generic authenticated_user allow/deny would run in Core but would not demonstrate the JIT/date mechanism, so it is intentionally not used.
